<section>
    <h2>Once we heard from stakeholders and users what they wanted, it was time to bring that to life.</h2>
    <p>Again, due to the limited time we'd have to test wireframes with users, we chose to focus on some key elements of the future app:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Logging in:</strong> Surprising complex, given all of the ways one can access their company's or university's Knovel subscription</li>
        <li><strong>Browsing materials:</strong> Users said they sometimes wanted a more curated experience, like other e-readers or online bookstores.</li>
        <li><strong>Searching materials:</strong> There were a lot of advanced search features on desktop that needed to make their way to the app.</li>
        <li><strong>Taking notes within materials:</strong> Again, previously only on desktop, but a key feature of any e-reader.</li>
        <li>Clearly and simply syncing user activity between desktop and mobile</li>
    </ul>

